This paper is primarily focused on cybersecurity threats to IoT devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of emulating IoT devices in honeypots, which involves networking and communication protocols (cs.NI) as well as software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the physical-connectedness nature of IoT devices, which could fall under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning to analyze attack data, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
